  "notes": "Upper Sorbian (Hornjoserbsce), West Slavic minority language of the Sorbian people in Lusatia, Germany. Palatal affricates ć /tɕ/ and dź /dʑ/ are distinctive. Ě = /jɛ/, ł = /w/. Dual grammatical number preserved.",
